-- HSBC Appoints Fautz Global Head of Mergers and Acquisitions
-- B y   A a r o n   K i r c h f e l d
-- 2013-09-04T12:44:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-04/hsbc-appoints-fautz-global-head-of-mergers-and-acquisitions.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Europe’s biggest
bank, named Florian Fautz as  global head  of mergers and
acquisitions.  Fautz, currently in charge of advisory for Germany, will
start his new job “in the near future,” Jezz Farr, a spokesman
for the London-based bank, said today. He’s filling the role of
Alain Renaud, who is on sabbatical, and will report to Spencer Lake, the head of capital financing.  Fautz joined HSBC in 2007 after working at Dresdner
Kleinwort. Reuters reported the appointment yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Kirchfeld in London at 
 akirchfeld@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
